WOODMERE CEMETERY ASSOCIATION v. COMMISSIONER OF INTERNAL REVENUE. No. 7547. Circuit Court of Appeals, Sixth Circuit. June 8, 1938. James K. Watkins, of Detroit, Mich., for petitioner. Robert H. Jackson, Sewall Key, Herman Oliphant, James W. Morris, Morrison Shafroth, and Frank M. Thompson, all of Washington, D. C., for respondent.

Before HICKS, SIMONS, and ALLEN, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

It is ordered that the appeal herein be and the same is dismissed, pursuant to stipulation of counsel.
